# Feishu Notifications

Main agent sends all notifications to avoid parent-child duplicates. Only notify at "start" and "handoff complete" boundaries, not for internal steps.

## When to Notify

| Scenario | event | Duration |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Subagent launched | `subagent_start` | No |
| Subagent finished (main continues) | `subagent_complete` | Yes, `--duration-ms` required |
| Main agent turn complete | `task_complete` | Yes, auto-reads session state |
| Main agent paused / awaiting user | `need_user_input` / `agent_stop` / `phase_complete` | No |

## Command

```bash
pnpm notify:feishu "<event>" "<result>; next: <action>" "<info|success|warning>"
```

## Timing Rules

- `task_complete`: auto-reads `sessionStart` hook state; pass `--duration-ms` or `--started-at-ms` when unavailable.
- `subagent_complete`: must explicitly pass `--duration-ms` or `--started-at-ms`; script aborts if missing.
- Timestamps in millisecond Unix time. Never hand-write or estimate duration in msg; script auto-appends human-readable duration.

## Constraints

- One notification per event; if parent already sent, child must not duplicate.
- `task_complete` is for main agent's final wrap-up only, not subagent completion.
- Duration labels: `subagent_complete` uses "subagent duration", `task_complete` uses "task duration"; never mix.
- Script auto-appends `task_id` (priority: `FEISHU_NOTIFY_TASK_ID` → `current-task.json` → `current-session.json`) and writes audit log to `logs/feishu-notify.log`.
